<span id="freeTextContainer10112682179281719989">Surprised by Tedium! Wow.....that’s 7 hours of my life I’ll never get back! As a teen I read and reread the Chronicles of Narnia...... wonderful books everyone should read........later on I read and enjoyed the Screwtape Letters. But this tedious, boring and over inflated autobiography was painful to read. If it wasn’t a book club pick I definitely would not have finished it! <br/>Perhaps I’m just not smart enough to get all the dropped obscure literature references. I also didn’t understand the poin</span>
  <span id="freeText10112682179281719989" style="display:none">Surprised by Tedium! Wow.....that’s 7 hours of my life I’ll never get back! As a teen I read and reread the Chronicles of Narnia...... wonderful books everyone should read........later on I read and enjoyed the Screwtape Letters. But this tedious, boring and over inflated autobiography was painful to read. If it wasn’t a book club pick I definitely would not have finished it! <br />Perhaps I’m just not smart enough to get all the dropped obscure literature references. I also didn’t understand the point of droning on ad nauseam about his childhood at boarding school. His long explanation of “bloods” and “fags” and his weird relationship with his father. <br />I found no joy whatsoever in this book. Would not recommend. </span>
