<div id="review_2654495437" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2654495437" />
    <a title="Beth Anne" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/4728103-beth-anne"><img alt="Beth Anne" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1564681652p2/4728103.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2654495437?book_show_action=true">Apr 01, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Beth Anne" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Beth Anne" href="/user/show/4728103-beth-anne">Beth Anne</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback " href="/book/show/8156170-surprised-by-joy">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4728103-beth-anne?shelf=audiobook">audiobook</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4728103-beth-anne?shelf=2020">2020</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2654495437" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17102155835959161294">Surprised by Joy was my final read for the month of March, a perfect timing book that I just loved. I listened to the audiobook thanks to the free @audible Stories, but often re-read sections in my own copy, underline and marking through the margins.<br/><br/>This is the story of Lewis’s childhood, being an atheist, growing as a young man and academic, and the gradual way that God drew him to Himself. The personal narrative of this book is conversational, the tone light even while the topics are deep. It </span>
  <span id="freeText17102155835959161294" style="display:none">Surprised by Joy was my final read for the month of March, a perfect timing book that I just loved. I listened to the audiobook thanks to the free @audible Stories, but often re-read sections in my own copy, underline and marking through the margins.<br /><br />This is the story of Lewis’s childhood, being an atheist, growing as a young man and academic, and the gradual way that God drew him to Himself. The personal narrative of this book is conversational, the tone light even while the topics are deep. It worked really well on audio, and I loved learning about the backstory of Lewis. Several moments in this book seemed to directly influence his writing in Voyage of the Dawn Treader, which I am currently listening to with my kids, and I enjoyed making those connections.</span>
  <a data-text-id="17102155835959161294" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


